  <summary>2/8/2000--Introduced.
State Children's Health Insurance Program Integrity Act of 2000 - Amends title XXI (Children's Health Insurance) of the Social Security Act to allow as reasonable administrative costs any State expenditures for the use of independent administrative vendors in marketing health benefits coverage to low-income children, or in otherwise administering the State child health plan, if certain conflict-of-interest restrictions are observed.</summary>
